{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"aeb4a55e-3420-458f-a0a2-2bf0f050f1b7","content":"Here's what needs to change:\n\n1. **Remove** the old assembly reference to `Microsoft.VisualStudio.QualityTools.UnitTestFramework`\n2. **Replace** the separate `Microsoft.NET.Test.Sdk` package with the unified `MSTest` v3 package (it bundles the framework, adapter, and test SDK)\n\nYour test code (`[TestClass]`, `[TestMethod]`, `Assert.*`, `[Timeout]`) is already compatible — no source changes needed.","toolRequests":[{"toolCallId":"toolu_vrtx_01YJYDJMY6PGmmnYw9nDzWUR","name":"report_intent","arguments":{"intent":"Upgrading to MSTest v3"},"type":"function"},{"toolCallId":"toolu_vrtx_013UQvgyxcdKiZZyccdkLGcE","name":"edit","arguments":{"path":"/tmp/sv-4cdd273a18fa4ef2a154aebd16c6adee/TestProject.csproj","old_str":"  <ItemGroup>\n    <Reference Include=\"Microsoft.VisualStudio.QualityTools.UnitTestFramework\" />\n  </ItemGroup>\n\n  <ItemGroup>\n    <PackageReference Include=\"Microsoft.NET.Test.Sdk\" Version=\"17.5.0\" />\n  </ItemGroup>","new_str":"  <ItemGroup>\n    <PackageReference Include=\"MSTest\" Version=\"3.8.0\" />\n  </ItemGroup>"},"type":"function","intentionSummary":"edit the file at /tmp/sv-4cdd273a18fa4ef2a154aebd16c6adee/TestProject.csproj."}],"interactionId":"4486f92c-57a3-41fc-a129-6cf392602348","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user has a .NET Framework test project that uses the old `Microsoft.VisualStudio.QualityTools.UnitTestFramework` assembly reference. They want to upgrade to MSTest v3.\n\nHere's what needs to change:\n\n1. **Remove the assembly reference** to `Microsoft.VisualStudio.QualityTools.UnitTestFramework`\n2. **Add the MSTest v3 NuGet package** — MSTest v3 consolidated everything into a single `MSTest` package (replacing `MSTest.TestFramework` + `MSTest.TestAdapter`)\n3. **Update the `Microsoft.NET.Test.Sdk`** version to a newer one (or keep it, but v3 may need a newer version)\n\n\n4. **Check the target framework** — MSTest v3 supports .NET Framework 4.6.2 and above, so most projects should be compatible. The namespace remains `Microsoft.VisualStudio.TestTools.UnitTesting`, so the test code itself shouldn't need changes beyond the reference swap.\n\nThe migration path is straightforward: replace the old assembly reference with a single `MSTest` package (v3.8.3 or later), which bundles the test framework, adapter, and SDK all together. This means I can remove both the legacy reference and the separate `Microsoft.NET.Test.Sdk` package dependency.\n\nThe existing test code already uses standard MSTest attributes and assertions that are fully compatible with v3, and since the project targets `net462`, which MSTest v3 supports, I can proceed with the upgrade.","outputTokens":1017,"requestId":"1BCF:DA0C6:A32A43:B843F3:6A03EB0D"},"id":"12c3088f-46d1-4113-acf0-bc0b234e14d5","timestamp":"2026-05-13T03:08:13.810Z","parentId":"08300800-fd70-4b17-89ea-80db0b133606"}
